Two loves I have, of comfort and despair,
That like two spirits do suggest me still.
My better angel is a man right fair,
But my worse is a dull spotless beauty.
He hath but a beard and a brow,
Which though he bear the name of a man,
Nor of any color, nor of any name,
Nor of any true name, but of a very short and
Excessful name.
But his name is my love, my true love,
Which, when I love him, I shall love his true love.
                                      


